Opel Seeks Profit Above 100 Million Euros, Automotive News Says

-- B y   K a r i n   M a t u s s e k
-- 
2011-07-09T10:46:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-09/opel-seeks-profit-above-100-million-euros-automotive-news-says.html
General Motors Co. (GM) ’s European Opel
unit aims to make a “substantial three-digit million euro
profit” in 2012, Automotive News  Europe  reported, citing
unidentified people at the company.  While Chief Executive Officer Karl-Friedrich Stracke
declined to confirm that number, he said the company seeks to
sell about 1.3 million cars in 2011, up from 1.2 million last
year, the magazine said in an e-mailed preview of the story.  Opel wants to reach an 8.5 percent market share in Europe
and more than 10 percent in Germany by the middle of the decade,
Stracke said in an interview with Automotive News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karin Matussek in Berlin at 
 kmatussek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at 
 aaarons@Bloomberg.net . 